The article is a presidential proclamation from November 23, 2010, declaring Thanksgiving Day as a National Day of Thanksgiving. The proclamation emphasizes the importance of Thanksgiving as a time to reflect on the grace and contributions of Native Americans, as well as to express gratitude for the year's blessings. It also highlights the historical significance of Thanksgiving, from the Pilgrims and Wampanoag tribe to President George Washington and President Abraham Lincoln. The proclamation acknowledges the sacrifices and service of the United States Armed Forces and encourages Americans to help those in need during the harvest season. President Barack Obama urges the people of the United States to come together in various settings to give thanks and share their bounty with others.